data.title: Home
data.meta_description: At Wade House, the golden era of carriages lives on. Experience Horse-Drawn Carriages and Historic Hospitality in Greenbush Wisconsin.
data.text:
Don't miss Wade House's 64th Annual Arts & Crafts Fair on Sunday, August 25 from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Besides the fantastic opportunity to admire and purchase wares from talented artists and craftsmen, the $5 Arts & Crafts Fair entry fee gets you FREE admission to the entire Wade House Historic Site. To take advantage of this special savings, guests should park off Center St. in Greenbush at W7824 Center Rd., the location of the Arts & Crafts Fair. Guests should NOT park at the Wade House Visitor Center on Hwy. 23. ... See MoreSee Less

“Feeding the world one pizza at a time…” is Frank Marzano’s slogan. Frank has been making pizzas since before grade school and took this passion to the next level with his wife Connie in 2001. If you’ve never tasted a Marzano Pizza Company pizza, Wade House has the perfect opportunity for you to do so. On Friday, August 23 between 4:30 p.m. and 8 p.m., Frank and Connie Marzano will be working their magic in the Wade House Visitor Center catering kitchen. They’ll be adding homemade sauce and a variety of ingredients to freshly prepared dough and baking the pizza pie to perfection. We promise the end product is worth the wait!

The pizza menu for Friday, August 23 includes: Sister Mari Margherita; Blake’s BBQ Blast; The S-M-O (sausage, mushroom and onion); Pepperoni; Sausage; 4 Cheese; Taco-Taco; Marzano Mac; and the Works.

Besides serving up medium ($18) and large ($22) pizzas, there will be refreshing beverages (beer, wine, lemonade, soda and water) as well as outdoor games to play as you wait for your freshly prepared pizza to bake to completion. Seating will be available outside on our Visitor Center patio and lawns as well as inside in our handsomely appointed Walnut Room. Let us know you’re coming by visiting our website at wadehouse.org

Hope to see you on August 23rd for our last Wade House Pizza Party of the season! ... See MoreSee Less

More than 50 of the regions' best artists and craftsmen will exhibit at Wade House's Arts & Crafts Fair on Sunday, August 25 from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. The exhibitors at this lively family friendly event employ a variety of mediums including painting, sculpture, ceramics, mixed media, printmaking, jewelry, fiber art, glass, wood, leather, metal and photography.

The $5 entry fee includes entrance to the Arts & Crafts Fair as well as FREE admission to the entire Wade House Historic Site, which includes a horse-drawn vehicle ride from the historic area to the Wade House Visitor Center and Wesley W. Jung Carriage Museum; a tour of the stately, 27-room stagecoach hotel; a trip to the Herrling Sawmill to see and feel the rumble of an up-and-down, water-powered saw; and a journey to the blacksmith's shop. Children ages 5 and under are FREE.

To take advantage of this special savings, guests should park off Center St. in Greenbush at W7824 Center Rd., the location of the Arts & Crafts Fair. Guests should NOT park at the Wade House Visitor Center on Hwy. 23. ... See MoreSee Less
